6:
Hee... Hahaha... You're fun to play
with...
11:
We've got you cornered. Surrender
now!
20:
The battlefield is no place for a child
like you.
33:
The coming of the Doomsday Lance
has left us with no choice and no
time. We must abandon this village
and join with the Resistance!
36: Make ready to leave by daybreak.
40:
...As for the girl, I will watch over her.
No one is to harm her without cause.
Do I make myself clear?
44: I would speak with you. But not here.
53: First, you must accept my apologies.
55:
I should have explained your
situation to the villagers... And I
should have listened to you, before I
attacked.
62:
I believe that the girl is not the
Harbinger of Death.
67:
But you do not believe that I am the
Champion Light.
69:
I cannot blame you. Not even a
shadow remains of my former self...
73:
Light would never let such defeat
creep into his voice.
76:
He was a proud man, who believed
that only he could master the tides
of this world. When he left on quests,
he scorned to take companions with
him.
78:
And he needed none! He was a
peerless warrior, unmatched in
strength or courage!
82:
Light would not abide sending
children onto the battlefield! He
would sooner die than... than...
88:
You do not need to accept me as
your champion. All I ask is that you
tell me what has befallen this world.
90: It is my duty to know.
97:
Space that is pierced by that lance
crumbles away, allowing
Pandemonium to mix with our
world...
100:
We witnessed a similar incident... in
Yamato...
104: Excelion was the first to fall...
106:
The land convulsed, as if seized by
the very throes of death. Buildings
tumbled and fire raged. And in the
midst of that destruction, the
daemons appeared.
112:
His last command to us was the
keeping of his daughter. But none of
us would have escaped with our
lives had another rift not formed...
114:
Connecting our world with
numerous others.
122:
There was a second tremor, and
even the servants of the Dark Throne
were tossed about like ragdolls.
124:
For fifty years now, this kingdom has
been colliding and mixing with alien
worlds.
127:
That must be why Sabre Peak froze
over...
131:
Wait... So everyone here knows that
there are multiple worlds?
134:
It has become just another fact of
life. Much of the Resistance is
beastfolk or longears. Neither are
native to our lands.
136:
But they have joined forces under
the leadership of Lilith. She has
much of her grandmother in her.
141: ...Do you think you can win this thing?
145:
There is not one among us that can
challenge the Lord of Shadow. He is
more similar to a great force of
nature than a living being.
147:
And each time the Doomsday Lance
appears, it drains our land of life.
Day by day, more daemons cross
our borders and fewer people are
left with homes.
155:
You won't have to wait long. All we
have to do is find the World Flipper,
and Light'll go back to his old self.
156: That's why we're here in the
166:
Don't tell me that all your plans
center around a fleeting dream. An
insubstantial belief.
170:
Or do you have proof that he will
indeed regain all his powers?
175:
There is no proof we can offer now.
But soon, I will be put to the test.
179:
Then until that time comes, do not
speak to the people of champions
or promises. Those words are like
poison.
182:
They dull the mind and paralyze the
limbs. Those who wait for a savior
soon forget how to save themselves.
186:
The people do not need some idol
to worship. They need a warrior to
fight and bleed alongside them.
189:
I will not stand in the way of your
quest. And, should you be in need of
guidance, Lilith may be able to aid
you.
191:
Though her kingdom lies in rubble,
royal blood still runs through her
veins. She may know things that we
do not.
196: We'll help you protect the refugees!
